Market Challenges
Regulatory Scrutiny on Copper Residues
Stringent limits on copper residues in food commodities have been imposed by several major agricultural jurisdictions. Compliance costs and the need for precise application timing create operational challenges for growers, potentially dampening market enthusiasm.

Other Challenges

Resistance Management
While copper resistance is relatively rare, isolated cases of pathogen adaptation have emerged. This is prompting the industry to develop rotation guidelines and combination strategies to preserve efficacy and mitigate resistance risks.

Emerging Opportunities
Global policy frameworks favouring sustainable agriculture, increased patient advocacy for effective crop protection, and strategic collaborations between agrochemists and research institutions are accelerating market expansion. Growing markets in Asia‑Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East & Africa represent key growth enablers, driven by enhanced regulatory environments, expanding infrastructure, and the pursuit of food security.

